name: R4B-DeviceDefinition-R5-DeviceDefinition
title: Concept map to convert a FHIR R4B DeviceDefinition into FHIR R5

element.display: An instance of a medical-related component of a medical device

target.display: An instance of a medical-related component of a medical device
target.comment: R4B `DeviceDefinition` maps as Equivalent to R5 `DeviceDefinition`

element.display: Extensions that cannot be ignored even if unrecognized

target.comment: R4B `DeviceDefinition.contact` maps as Equivalent to R5 `DeviceDefinition.contact`
R4B `DeviceDefinition.contained` maps as Equivalent to R5 `DeviceDefinition.contained`

element.display: A name given to the device to identify it

target.display: The name or names of the device as given by the manufacturer
target.comment: R4B `DeviceDefinition.deviceName` maps as Equivalent to R5 `DeviceDefinition.deviceName`

R4B `DeviceDefinition.deviceName.extension` maps as RelatedTo to R5 `DeviceDefinition.deviceName.extension` - extension has change due to type change: R4B `extension` `Extension` maps as RelatedTo for R5 `extension`
R4B `DeviceDefinition.deviceName.id` maps as Equivalent to R5 `DeviceDefinition.deviceName.id`

element.display: Extensions that cannot be ignored even if unrecognized

target.display: A name that is used to refer to the device

element.display: udi-label-name | user-friendly-name | patient-reported-name | manufacturer-name | model-name | other

target.comment: R4B `DeviceDefinition.deviceName.type` maps as SourceIsNarrowerThanTarget to R5 `DeviceDefinition.deviceName.type` - type has compatible required binding for code type: http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/device-nametype|4.3.0 and http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/device-nametype|5.0.0 (SourceIsNarrowerThanTarget)

R4B `DeviceDefinition.id` maps as Equivalent to R5 `DeviceDefinition.id`
R4B `DeviceDefinition.identifier` maps as Equivalent to R5 `DeviceDefinition.identifier`

target.comment: R4B `DeviceDefinition.implicitRules` maps as Equivalent to R5 `DeviceDefinition.implicitRules`

target.display: Language code for the human-readable text strings produced by the device (all supported)
